100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 4, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing tensions surrounding disarmament and international cooperation. In the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition continued to stir public sentiment, with calls for reform gaining traction. Meanwhile, in Britain, the government announced plans to increase funding for housing to address the post-war housing crisis.
